  "description": [
    "Page Eight LETTERBOX Continued from Page Three Reynauds and Petains who sold out France and liberty to ever have been considered as champi ons of democracy For two and a half years the Spanish republi cans with little or no arms held out against these same fascist barbarians yet the French gen erals with much more at their command gave not even the pre tense of resistance The truth of the matter is that the French Rightist government was never democratic in the first place What they cherished most were the financial interest of France and not the democratic li berties of the French people For when the French people were suc cessful in electing the Popular Front these same betrayers of France fought against the peoples newly won reforms What the Peoples Front government gained for the people through parliament these collaborators with fascism later nullified by swift decrees in the interest of national defense When France could have cinched a republican victory in Spain by selling the legitimately elected Spanish government arms the move was sabotaged by these same reactionary vultures who cared more for a fascist victory than a republican one The two hundred families who rule"
  ],
